SIMPLE: humiliation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Humiliation
<hw>Hu*mil`i*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>humiliatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>humiliation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of humiliating or humbling; abasement of pride;
mortification.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Hopkins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being humiliated, humbled, or reduced
to lowliness or submission.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The former was a <qex>humiliation</qex> of Deity; the latter a
<qex>humiliation</qex> of manhood.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Humility</ent>⟦br⟧
